orangelight.title: RTL display issue - the table in browselists displays the rtl languages in the wrong place. The same issue exists in the record page.

comments.body:
It looks like only the title field has the `rtl` class, even though other fields have Arabic (non-transliterated) values (e.g. creator, publication info). 

Even though the title field has a `rtl` class, it seems to be wrapping on the left side, which seems like would be a major aspect of rtl display? Unfortunately, I'm not familiar with any rtl languages, so can't tell how legible the rtl display is. 

title wrapping example
![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5d51624a5b89150001ae0b03/b591103e-9af5-446d-a4f2-f9d96624ecbd)

publication info wrapping example
![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5d51624a5b89150001ae0b03/995fa197-740b-4f8b-b9cf-73f86e6cb3f5)

From team discussion:
* The label should be left-anchored
* The title itself should be right-anchored, and should wrap on the right side
